cs.CY, cs.CE, cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.NI

Reasoning: 

- cs.CY (Computers and Society): The paper discusses the use of mobile phones and community sensing to monitor crop health in a developing nation, which has implications for the social and economic aspects of the community. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper describes the development of a modified mobile ad hoc surveillance ecosystem for data collection and communication, which involves computational engineering and science. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper may touch on security concerns related to the collection and sharing of real-time surveillance data on cassava. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper discusses the use of community sensing and mobile phones to collect data from smallholder farmers, which involves social and information networks. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper describes the communication model and data collection model designed for the scale of surveillance, which involves networking and internet architecture.
